          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search          Glencraig is a very small former mining village in Scotland, situated in the Benarty area of Fife, between Crosshill and Lochgelly. The village's population has decreased significantly since the decline of the coal-mining industry during the 1970s and 1980s.[1] References[edit]   ^ http://www.glencraig.org/About/about.html        This article relies largely or entirely upon a single source. Relevant discussion may be found on the talk page. Please help improve this article by introducing citations to additional sources. (July 2010)      Wikimedia Commons has media related to Glencraig.   Coordinates: 56°08′26″N 3°19′11″W﻿ / ﻿56.1406°N 3.3197°W﻿ / 56.1406; -3.3197     This Scottish location article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e                         Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Glencraig&oldid=636166347"          Categories: Villages in FifeScotland geography stubsHidden categories: Articles needing additional references from July 2010All articles needing additional referencesCommons category with page title same as on WikidataCoordinates on WikidataAll stub articles            
